OL,3,C'Indefensible abuse' of rivers
OL,4,Ccriticised by Archbishop of Wales
OL,6,FDuring a meeting held in Newport, he
OL,7,Ftold members of the Church in Wales
OL,8,Fthat raw sewage and farming practices
OL,9,Fwere killing rivers, referring to the
OL,10,F"tragic" situation in the Wye Valley.
OL,12,FIn 2023, pollution levels in the River
OL,13,FWye led to its status being
OL,14,Freclassified from "unfavourable-
OL,15,Fimproving" to "unfavourable-
OL,16,Fdeclining", with key species like
OL,17,Fsalmon and white-clawed crayfish
OL,18,Fexperiencing decline.
